<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1168328252573">
<term>neap tide</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1168327962003">low tide created when the Moon and the Sun form a right triangle with Earth</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1168327903551">
<term>spring tide</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1168327963906">high tide created when the Moon, the Sun, and Earth are along one line</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1168328265438">
<term>tidal force</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1168328175497"><emphasis effect="italics">difference</emphasis> between the gravitational force at the center of a body and that at any other location on the body; the tidal force stretches the body</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
